example.pre:
Situation one: Category smart pointer is passed to function as parameter, IsValid is needed to validate.For example: 
void Foo(CategoryRef& senderRef)
{
    if (!senderRef.IsValid()) { //invokes IsValid method to validate category smart pointer senderRef.
        assert(0 && "senderRef is invalid.");
        return;
    }
    бнбн
}

Situation two: Category smart pointer is converted from i2i function, IsValid method is needed to check.For example: 
CategoryRef cCategoryRef

//interface smart pointer IXXXRef already points to Category object, through which we can obtain corresponding category smart pointer
CategoryRef cCategoryRef = i2i(IXXXRef);

if (!cCategoryRef.IsValid()) { //validate category smart pointer cCategoryRef by invoking IsValid method.
    assert(0 && "cCategoryRef is invalid.");
    return 1;
}
